			<ns0:name>mark@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mark@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">As for why this happens only in x86-64 debug, I think it&#8217;s because the time that it takes to operate on the new Mach thread map. That map doesn&#8217;t exist in x86-32. It has additional DCHECKs that run in debug mode to ensure map integrity. Running those checks probably tickles the timing so that the test is flaky on x86-64 debug, but seems stable in other configurations.

If my theory is correct, the test is actually flaky in all configurations, but x86-64 debug is the one where the timings make it such that failures are actually observed.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-03-13T16:17:52.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-03-13T16:17:52.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 5 by mark@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3336#c5" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3336/comments/full/5" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>